<h2>Running Tests</h2>

<p>If you provide no arguments, Lens will run all of your tests:</p>

<div class="terminal">
	<div>Run all of your tests:</div>
	<pre><code>lens</code></pre>
</div>

<p>But if you provide one or more paths, Lens will run <i>only</i> the tests at those locations:</p>

<div class="terminal">
	<div>Run some of your tests:</div>
	<pre><code>lens <i>MyFile.php</i> <i>MyDirectory</i></code></pre>
</div>


<h2>Reports</h2>

<p>Lens can provide reports in different formats.
This is mainly useful for integrating with third-party tools:</p>

<div class="terminal">
	<div>Generate an <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/XUnit">xUnit</a> report:</div>
	<pre><code>lens --report=xunit</code></pre>
</div>

<div class="terminal">
	<div>Generate a <a href="https://testanything.org/">TAP</a> report:</div>
	<pre><code>lens --report=tap</code></pre>
</div>


<h2>Version</h2>

<div class="terminal">
	<div>View the version information</div>
	<pre><code>lens --version</code></pre>
</div>

<p>Is your version of Lens up to date?
Here are the current <a href="https://github.com/Spencer-Mortensen/lens/releases">releases</a> for comparison.</p>